%feature("docstring") OT::DualBootstrapExperiment
"Bootstrap with two samples.

DualBootstrapExperiment allows resampling with the bootstrap method from two
samples of the same size with consistent ordering.
It allows for example to draw samples from input/output samples.

Parameters
----------
sample1, sample2 : 2-d sequence of float
    Source samples, must have the same size

See also
--------
BootstrapExperiment

Examples
--------
>>> import openturns as ot
>>> ot.RandomGenerator.SetSeed(0)
>>> size = 5
>>> x = ot.Normal(2).getSample(size)
>>> y = ot.Normal(1).getSample(size)
>>> experiment = ot.DualBootstrapExperiment(x, y)
>>> x1, y1 = experiment.generate()"

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------

%feature("docstring") OT::DualBootstrapExperiment::GenerateSelection
"Generate a list of indices of points with replacement.

Parameters
----------
size : positive int
    Size of the set of indices in which the indices are chosen.
length : positive int
    Number of indices to choose.

Returns
-------
selection : :class:`~openturns.Indices`
    Sequence of size *length* of indices :math:`i` such that :math:`0\leq i<size`.
"
